{"questionId":"9067513","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Automobile air bags inflate by a rapid decomposition reaction. One typical compound used is guanidinium nitrate, C(NH<sub>2</sub>)<sub>3</sub>NO<sub>3</sub>, which decomposes very rapidly to form nitrogen, water vapour and carbon.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Calculate the total number of moles of gas produced from the decomposition of 10.0 g of guanidinium nitrate.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">moles of gas = « <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{10.0{\\text{g}}}}{{122.11{\\text{g mo}}{{\\text{l}}^{ - 1}}}}\"><mn>5</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>10.0</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>g</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>122.11</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>g mo</mtext><msup><mtext>l</mtext><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo></math></span>» 0.409 «mol» ✔</span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067513","referenceCode":"19N.2.sl.TZ0.6a(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the total number of moles of gas produced from the decomposition of 10.0 g of guanidinium nitrate.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 1: Stoichiometric relationships","1.2 The mole concept","Core","Topic 1: Stoichiometric relationships"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}